  "title": "Refinement List - Shows wrong items when 'Show More' is enabled.",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nIt appears that the start index of items to display on a refinement list when 'Show More' is enabled is not at the top of the items list.  Rather near the middle or even bottom.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nView an example of this bug at my JSFiddle.  https://jsfiddle.net/jandk4014/aq9Laaew/234880/.  It wouldn't make sense for me to add my code to this ticket.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe expected result for this refinement list would be to start with the first item in the list.  In this example if would be 1/8\".  However, as you can see it's starting near the bottom of the listed items.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\nWhat I currently show.  It shows 4 (1/4\") as the first item.  This is incorrect.\r\n<img width=\"303\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-24 at 12 56 23 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3721279/45975527-521a0900-bff9-11e8-80bb-d51f29567abb.png\">\r\n\r\nWith the list fully expanded you can see that 1/8\" is at the top of the list and should be shown as such.\r\n<img width=\"319\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-24 at 12 56 35 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3721279/45975574-6cec7d80-bff9-11e8-82ef-1f219e61957d.png\">\r\n\r\n",
